                <div class="highlight-box">
                    <h3>What Makes ACII Different?</h3>
                    <p>The ACII is very different from Certificates and Diplomas because students are mostly tested on <strong>applying their knowledge</strong> rather than simply remembering content. Unlike the earlier qualifications where tests focus on recall and comprehension, in ACII, the examiners want to hear your thoughts, opinions, and strategic analysis.</p>
